title: July 20, 2001 - Larry Miller
description: The Daily Show becomes the first late night show to need airbags. At the G-8 summit, the world's most powerful nations come together in the name of peace and good will; what could go wrong? Mo Rocca takes measure of the great energy debate. "Consumptionists" unveil their own mascot, Robosaurus. Walt Disney buys Fox Family for $3.2 billion; Jon hopes they buy his family next. And if you're his wife, sex with Larry Miller could be hazardous to your health.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 24, 2001 - Paul Giamatti
description: Jon can't name all of the members of 'N Sync. The U.S. stands up to peer pressure and refuses to endorse the Kyoto treaty. Steve Carell gets a language lesson in Klingon, while Lewis Black covers some strange summertime activities. Paul Giamatti describes the sexual tension between him and a monkey and a crocodile placed in an Australian pool makes kids swim faster.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 25, 2001 - Joe Lieberman
description: Jon celebrates five years of fake news with The Daily Show Fifth Anniversary Special. Unfortunately, none of the correspondents are able to be here, but they've all recorded special video messages. As part of the oft-maligned media, Jon takes a look at what it really means to be part of a feeding frenzy. Senator Joe Lieberman joins Jon via satellite to talk about what he's been doing since the 2000 presidential election and what he thinks of the Bush administration so far. Jon premieres the new Daily Show anthem: "Pride of America."
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 26, 2001 - John McCain
description: John Ashcroft makes the cover of the NRA's magazine for hyping the Second Amendment. Jon interviews John McCain about his friendship with President Bush, campaign finance reform and a possible 2004 presidential run. Matt Walsh interviews centenarian Anna Wilmot about her plans for dealing with the thief that stole the oars to her rowboat. Jon profiles a hero pig who saved his owner from muggers, and Mo Rocca reviews a production of "The Nutcracker" that's almost cruel in its beauty.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 30, 2001 - Jerri Manthey
description: Former president Bill Clinton moves his new office to Harlem, New York and correspondent Stephen Colbert reports. Lance Armstrong wins his third straight Tour de France and correspondent Matt Walsh provides coverage from Paris. Survivor cast member Jerri Manthey discusses her Playboy spread.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 31, 2001 - Peter Krause
description: Jon would love a mulligan on his intro to today's show. Global computer warfare is here, and if Jon doesn't look panicked, it's only because he can't act. In this era of the news becoming the news, have we hit the breaking point yet? Rock and Roll is suffering from a shortage of drummers. If Charlton Heston wears a loin cloth to the next NRA meeting Frank DeCaro will join, and Peter Krause would have liked to give Jon some wood or leather for the anniversary of his third year on the show.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 1, 2001 - Jackie Chan
description: The House of Representatives places a ban on human cloning to the chagrin of the League of American Mad Scientists. A man puts his child's name up for auction on eBay, and his mother is rooting for Microsoft. Stephen Colbert investigates whether "Planet of the Apes" could actually happen by going undercover as a gorilla. After Mt. Etna erupts, Sicilians work to save their mothers' buildings. Jackie Chan tells Jon Stewart about his influences in American film and about running naked in the streets of Hong Kong.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 2, 2001 - Janeane Garofalo
description: MTV hosts an awesome gala to celebrate its 20th anniversary, while The Daily Show correspondents hold a rap session in the Kickin' It Lounge. The EPA forces GE to clean up the Hudson, Lewis Black wonders why man competes and Janeane Garofalo discusses David Hyde Pierce's soft lips.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 6, 2001 - Andie MacDowell
description: It's "opposites day" at The Daily Show. President Bush looks forward to a little R&R, because that's what letter he's up to in his penmanship workbook. Shouldn't celebrities be allowed to tell us how to grow old gracefully, even sexily? The triangular design of Wilt Chamberlain's house makes it much easier to dust, with your penis. Jon thinks Andie MacDowell smells better than most of the show's guests. A mysterious sea creature washes up on a Canadian beach; see what happens when you don't cut your six-pack holders, people. In ancient times left-handers were considered demons and burned at the stake, and Jon likes the 2,000 pound magenta triangular front door at Wilt Chamberlain's house.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 7, 2001 - Joe Rogan
description: Italian scientists announce they will clone a human, then take it to the Olive Garden where they'll treat it like family. Bill Clinton snags a $10 million book deal -- why that's forty thousand massages with release. If your grandparents ever use the expression "early bird special" then you know they've had someone killed before dawn. Flying all the way around the world in a balloon is a dream for anyone who has flown part way around the world in a balloon, and Jon probably still owes Joe Rogan lunch money despite them never having gone to school together.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 8, 2001 - Tara Reid
description: Jon Stewart reports on the record heat wave in New York City and meteorologist Matt Walsh checks on the weather around the country. Correspondent Steve Carell gives tips on how to beat the heat. Tara Reid discusses her new movie, "American Pie 2." Commentator Lewis Black talks about a rubber band ball and a Japanese music group. Jon Stewart previews Catastrophe Week on NBC.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 9, 2001 - Jason Biggs
description: President George W. Bush is on vacation in Texas and correspondent Stephen Colbert visits a misunderstood small town. Steve Carell and Nancy Walls love show business and actor Jason Biggs discusses the versatility of his penis.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 13, 2001 - David Rakoff
description: It was 20 years ago this week that the computer error message replaced the useless TV antenna as the main source of household violence. Can George W. Bush appease moderate swing voters without alienating his conservative power base? He doesn't know what it is, but Steve Carell is for stem cell research. David Rakoff explains marketing of cars. The unicorns needed by NASA to fulfill their delusional fantasy will be unavailable due to a previous commitment to kissing rainbows, and commercials geared to Generation X'ers have Steve Carell longing to Splode!
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 14, 2001 - John Carpenter
description: Jon Stewart discovers that the newest trend in broadcast news is to look good, then examines the resurgence of the Zeppelin in Germany. Senior Relationship Correspondents Steve Carell and Nancy Walls tell you how you're ruining your relationships and John Carpenter talks about drugs, Peter Fonda and Martian ghosts.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 15, 2001 - Seth Green
description: Stephen Colbert covers President Bush's stay at his family's compound in Crawford, Texas. Seth Green stops by to talk about his film, "Rat Race." The children of high ranking republicans are getting high - profile government jobs, and the Chess Federation makes a plea chess to be an Olympic sport. Steve Carell previews what will happen on tomorrow's Produce Pete.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 16, 2001 - Fabio
description: Finally the question of why you never see Fabio and Jon Stewart in the same place will be answered. Fresh off his 30 day vacation, President Bush takes a two day sub-vacation in Colorado. With its beach goers slathered in coconut scented suntan oil, it's no surprise that 50% of unprovoked shark attacks happen in Florida. An unprecedented shark summit in Florida, a G-8 for Predators. It's been settled, the Swiss aren't neutral by choice, it's just that no one wants them on their side, and Fabio isn't from any country.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 20, 2001 - Cuba Gooding, Jr
description: U.S. News & World Report's annual "Best Colleges" issue comes under fire, while Steve Carell profiles a minister who believes that dancing is morally dangerous. Johnny Knoxville quits MTV's "Jackass," Frank DeCaro reviews "American Pie 2," and Cuba Gooding Jr. discusses his new movie, "Rat Race."
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 21, 2001 - Griffin Dunne
description: Jon is hardly a religious scholar, but he thought when you have a Bar Mitzvah you're supposed to do Jewish stuff. A check-in with our perpetually vacationing president. The Power Ball jackpot is $200 million, come on all ones! It's a good economy, it works hard, and when people don't have confidence in it, it hurts. Shark attacks are up this summer because people taste good. Griffin Dunne called in cameo favors to Charlie Sheen and Spike Lee, who regretted it but showed up, and tomorrow Matt Walsh visits the refugees of Centralia.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 22, 2001 - Will Ferrell
description: Grimace is beheaded in the chaotic wake left by fraud at McDonald's. Norway's new "first honorable regimental sergeant major" is a penguin. We take a trip to coal country, and Will Ferrell says that "Jay and Silent Bob Strike Back" is a fun romp.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 23, 2001 - Kevin Smith
description: North Carolina Senator Jesse Helms retires at the age of 79 and correspondent Mo Rocca investigates the difference between mainstream and indie cat films. Actor/director Kevin Smith talks about Jon Stewart's role in the children's video, "Elmopalooza." Lewis Black lists a few things we don't need: pet psychics, Lithuanians dancing to American country music, strongest beard records and Al Gore.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 10, 2001 - They Might Be Giants
description: President Bush details his plan to reverse the unemployment rate, Steve Carell examines sex in advertising, and They Might Be Giants reminisces about an old New Jersey venue.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 20, 2001
description: The first episode back after the World Trade Center attacks on 9/11. Jon Stewart introduces the night's show, all repeat pieces, which he hopes will put a smile on people's faces. Correspondent Vance DeGeneres interviews presidential candidate Charles R. Doty. Jon spends a day at the Republican National Convention with Peter Jennings. Steve Carell reports on a new hair removal product.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 24, 2001 - Frank Rich
description: On the second Daily Show after the 9/11 attacks, Jon Stewart is doing his patriotic duties. New York Times columnist Frank Rich discusses the complicated emotions of the American people. Jon Stewart reports on new studies involving chocolate and puberty. Senior Produce Analyst Steve Carell gives tips on how to make your fall dishes taste exotic. Correspondent Mo Rocca presents a behind the scenes look at the Green Mountain Hot Shots.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 25, 2001 - Aaron Brown
description: Fox has decided the best way to honor America is to broadcast a show called "Who Wants to be a Princess?" Jon is appalled and intrigued. Stephen Colbert has exclusive insight into the plane flight taken by the winners of "Who Wants to be a Princess?" and wonders how long their love will last. Aaron Brown visits the show to talk about covering September 11th for CNN.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 26, 2001 - Jeff Greenfield
description: Steve Carell and Nancy Walls present the new fall television schedule. Jeff Greenfield discusses the cultural and social ramifications of the 9/11 attacks. Lewis Black reports on his recent trip across the country.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 27, 2001 - Tenacious D
description: Jon Stewart reports that irony is dead. Michael Jordan returns to professional basketball and Veteran Analyst Steve Carell offers his opinion. Tenacious D rocks out. A Chinese panda celebrates her birthday, and Frank DeCaro reviews "Glitter."
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 1, 2001 - Kelsey Grammer
description: Jon learns that the new look for fall is the gas mask and biohazard suit. Searching for citizens of Leathervania. An extraordinary leader, Rudy Giuliani tells the people exactly what they want to hear. Kelsey Grammer was once a convenient story device, and an excerpt from the Royal Journal of Lackluster Sound Bytes.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 2, 2001 - Jim Belushi
description: The Taliban want to see proof that Osama bin Laden was responsible for 9/11. The Supreme Court disbars former President Clinton for lying under oath, and Stephen Colbert learns a thing or two about what it means to be a television anchor at the prestigious Connecticut School of Broadcasting. Daily Show resident hacker Lord Viper Scorpion explores the world of online shopping, and Jim Belushi talks "According to Jim" and the House of Blues Hotel.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 3, 2001 - Stephen Morse
description: Jon explains how The Daily Show is able to move seamlessly between such diverse topics. Osama bin Laden's life story is told and Stephen Colbert explores the various disguises bin Laden employs to remain hidden. Dr. Stephen Morse tells Jon to relax, Steve Carell has some pretty lame exotic animals and the mole people will rule the earth.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 4, 2001 - Kate Beckinsale
description: Jon wants to see how MSNBC reporter Ashleigh Banfield fares against the Taliban's gaydar. Lauren Weedman wants Banfield's job and she is more than happy to do anything for it. Stephen Colbert, Steve Carell, Mo Rocca and Nancy Walls all share their tips on blending in as international correspondents. Kate Beckinsale isn't married, but she does have kids. Katherine Harris is running for Congress, Matt Walsh wants to avoid the harsh realities of fall and Mo Rocca dresses up as Christopher Columbus.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 9, 2001 - Owen Wilson
description: The army asks the writers of MacGyver and others in Hollywood to brainstorm some potential terrorist plots. Matt Walsh and Lauren Weedman report from a dark room that they pretend is Afghanistan. Mo Rocca recaps the journey of Christopher Columbus up Columbus Avenue, and Owen Wilson explains the brainstorming process behind hip-hop male models.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 10, 2001 - Jeremy Piven
description: Geri Halliwell travels to Afghanistan to entertain the troops in the middle of the desert without the aid of complex carbohydrates. Stephen Colbert takes a look at the food being provided to the Afghani refugees and suggests something with more zazz like a fondu. Steve Carell is enjoying the food meant for the refugees just fine. Great Britain becomes the first country to include Jedi Knight as a religion on their census forms and Steve Carell takes a look at an infomercial that finally combines the coin and bear collector demographics. Jeremy Piven discusses his new movie "Serendipity" and the evils of unleavened bread.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 11, 2001 - John Miller
description: "Survivor" is back on the air because what we need as a country right now is real people coping with fake crises. In a new reality show, Hollywood producers are locked in a house for three months and forced to come up with more ideas for reality TV. Al Jazeera nabs the exclusive on bin Laden's recent taped statement and John Miller talks about interviewing Osama bin Laden.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 15, 2001 - Emeril Lagasse
description: America freaks out over anthrax. Steve Carell and Stephen Colbert debate on how much the public needs to know about the war in Afghanistan. Baboons are capable of learning complex mental tasks involving abstract reasoning, Matt Walsh knows how to get gum out of the carpet, and Emeril Lagasse cooks all the time.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 16, 2001 - Lorraine Bracco
description: Senator Tom Daschle's is office shut down because of the anthrax scare, and Steve Carell takes a look at how the media avoids scaremongering. Japanese company Omron introduces Necoro, the robotic cat. Matt Walsh interviews concerned mother Terri Birkett about her apprehension towards Dr. Seuss, and Lorraine Bracco talks to Jon about her movie, "Riding in Cars with Boys."
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 17, 2001 - Snoop Dogg
description: Jon Stewart doesn't think the Anthrax scare in New York will work because New Yorkers are accustomed to biological threats. The Bush Administration uses diplomacy and propaganda to convince Muslim countries to be our allies. Mo Rocca analyzes CNN's six questions for Osama bin Laden. Stephen Colbert examines the phenomenon of "Girl's Gone Wild," and Jon interviews rapper Snoop Dogg.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 18, 2001 - Fareed Zakaria
description: Jon swears like an elf over the anthrax scare, while more anthrax cases pop up in New York. Since 9/11, everyone's been talking about macaroni and cheese. Steve Carell can't stop eating comfort food and Fareed Zakaria talks to Jon about why the Middle East hates America.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 22, 2001 - Lance Bass
description: Superstar musicians from around the globe throw concerts in New York and Washington to raise the nation's spirits after the September 11th attacks. At the Concert for D.C., Matt Walsh is wowed by James Brown -- and no one else. MC Hammer records a new single to pay tribute to the victims of the September 11th attacks. Stephen Colbert reports live from ground zero on a second, even more horrendous attack on American soil. Steve Carell profiles Emery Harriston, a 39-year-old baton twirler, and Lance Bass discusses singing with 'N SYNC and acting for the first time in "On the Line."
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 23, 2001 - Don Dahler
description: The post-9/11 economic climate burdens companies and trade expos, Lauren Weedman exposes the wild side of Amish life, and Don Dahler discusses the Taliban in Afghanistan.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 24, 2001 - Greta Van Susteren
description: President George W. Bush attends the Asian Pacific Economic Cooperation Summit in Shanghai, China. Foreign Affairs Correspondent Nancy Walls presents the new Daily Show map center. Greta Van Susteren discusses the anthrax situation. Commentator Lewis Black reports on Starbucks' in Houston, Texas.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 25, 2001 - Jeff Bridges
description: It's spore distribution weather today in New York. Who said the art of letter writing is dead. Lacking a unicorn sticker, the anthrax letters sent to Tom Daschle and Tom Brokaw were definitely not written by a little girl. Jeff Bridges is a really, really good liar. The hottest news coming out of Hollywood, and Steve Carell checks out a haunted house.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 30, 2001 - Rob Morrow
description: John Ashcroft plays the part of the "buzz kill." Supreme Court Justices are forced to drink from ordinary drinking glasses. Highest level of alert means you can't get any more alert, it's pretty straight forward. Steve Carell doesn't feel scared by a haunted house, but he does feel cheated, and when planning to direct his new movie, "Maze," Rob Morrow was apprehensive about casting himself, as he didn't think he'd get along with him.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: October 31, 2001 - Richard Holbrooke
description: America is temporarily distracted by the World Series before realizing that it's in a massive recession. Steve Carell and Matt Walsh prefer to think of the latest recession as a period of "pre - growth." Former ambassador to the United Nations Richard Holbrooke discusses American foreign policy post - 9/11. Lewis Black discovers new trends in hippopotamus feed, a domestic python and a screaming contest in Thailand.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 1, 2001 - Kevin Spacey
description: Americans vow not to let fear stop them from being terrified on Halloween. Matt Walsh travels to Afghanistan to find out if Osama bin Laden dresses up his pets. Steve Carell finds out that everyone has a story, even if they might not have a point. Kevin Spacey talks to Jon about his new movie, "K - Pax." Jon profiles the giant panda Ying Ying in an effort to answer the eternal question: why do the pandas hate us?
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 5, 2001 - Paul Rudd
description: Jon gets freaked out at the site of 30,000 people running at him on the streets of New York. Geraldo Rivera is going to Afghanistan to cover the war on terror. Congress is debating two separate aviation security bills, both of which, according to Stephen Colbert, are awful. Steve Carell has been making a tour of the nation's airports and has had some unfortunate run-ins regarding his love of Diet Coke. The Salem Witches have finally been exonerated, Lauren Weedman loves New York, and Paul Rudd has four nipples.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 6, 2001 - P.J. O'Rourke
description: Having the characters of "Buffy the Vampire Slayer" break out into song and dance really breaks the reality of the show for Jon. Seven knives, a stun gun and pepper spray get by airport security in Chicago. An amazing breakthrough for anthrax patients on the go. In the world of bio-terrorism, anthrax is on everyone's mind. Frank DeCaro wishes he waited for "K-PAX" to come out on video, and P.J. O'Rourke wants you to know that we're on alert, we just don't know what for.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 7, 2001 - George Stephanopoulos
description: It's the day after Election Day 2001 and a few people actually care. Jon reports on how Michael Bloomberg ran a grassroots campaign using limited resources. Steve Carell is so caught up in war reporting that he has trouble shifting gears. Melissa Gilbert wins the all - important SAG Presidency. Stephen Colbert likes the idea of a monarchy and George Stephanopoulos tries to make sense of the New York elections and the Middle East.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 8, 2001 - Jennifer Saunders
description: America attempts to return to normalcy with car chases and flights on the Concorde. Correspondent Matt Walsh reports on Michael Jackson's latest release. The movie "Harry Potter and the Sorcerer's Stone" premieres in London, England. Steve Carell investigates news channel advertising. Actress Jennifer Saunders promotes the return of her television show, "Absolutely Fabulous."
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 12, 2001 - Steve Kroft
description: The nation's top food scientists are hard at work making tastier Meals Ready To Eat kits for the troops. Steve Kroft explains that news networks need a big story. Steve Carell looks at the most effective way to add drama to the news.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 13, 2001 - Anne Robinson
description: Jon offers a little love advice to the audience. Stephen Colbert reports live from Afghanistan, where citizens celebrate the arrival of the Northern Alliance in Kabul. Hollywood's entertainment executives work with government officials to help boost troop morale. "The Home Front" propaganda reel extols the virtues of average Americans who sacrifice absolutely nothing to support the war effort. Jon reviews letters from pop culture magazine editors responding to September 11th and the latest series of Topps baseball cards. "Produce Pete" offers some Thanksgiving succotash tips. Anne Robinson namedrops a few of the more prominent and dumbest contestants on "The Weakest Link."
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 14, 2001 - Carson Daly
description: All the taxis in the city of Kabul are driven by guys named Kevin. The liberation of Afghanistan has its people dancing in the streets, to the Macarena. A creation scientist in Texas declares that dinosaurs and man were created to live together and were friends. Be forewarned terrorists -- we will find you -- so long as your point of departure is Fresno, California, and Carson Daly is convinced a side show is going on in the streets of Times Square during TRL.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 15, 2001 - John Stamos
description: The Harry Potter phenomenon has hit the Daily Show, as the first movie nears release. Steve Carell surrenders and gives Harry Potter five white flags. Frank DeCaro compares the book to the movie, admitting it doesn't matter in the end. Vlaidimir Putin visits President Bush at his ranch in Texas for a Jackson Browne sing-along. Lewis Black longs for the days of sensationalistic newscasts focusing on the likes of Gary Condit and sharks, and John Stamos curses up a storm.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 26, 2001 - Edward Burns
description: It's a Thanksgiving recap! After thoroughly stuffing himself, Jon reminds us all about the confusing sectarian violence in newly liberated Afghanistan. Stephen Colbert chimes in from Kabul to offer an enlightening examination of Afghan tribal traditions. Jon brings us back stateside with an intimate look at the Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade and Mo Rocca decides that there really is no place like home. Guest Edward Burns makes fun of Jon's dog. Welcome back to the America we know and love!
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 27, 2001 - Star Jones
description: The United States gives the Taliban $43 million in aide to fight the drug war. The Department of Justice invites Middle Eastern citizens for interviews. Doctors are cloning human embryos to help fight disease. Correspondent Matt Walsh enters the dark world of illegal sports. Steve Carell provides highlights of TV commercial acting. Star Jones gives a behind the scenes look of "The View."
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 28, 2001 - Jennifer Garner
description: The sport of boxing returns to Afghanistan. Attorney General Ashcroft talks about keeping information from Al Qaeda. The American people are reportedly happy with American news agencies. Steve Carell reports about news tickers. Killer owls are the latest craze this holiday season. Lewis Black discusses airline security measures, and Jennifer Garner talks about her show, Alias.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: November 29, 2001 - David Halberstam
description: Jon wets his teeth on this year's Hanukah controversy and then turns his attention to all the people watching a tree being lit up for Jesus. Two grown men squabble over a ball in San Francisco, and Stacey Grenrock Woods interviews a man hell bent on stopping illegal bingo. Steve Carell and Mo Rocca recommend excessive generosity this holiday season to alleviate the strains of the recession, and David Halberstam talks about the U.S.'s isolationist tendencies since the end of the Cold War.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: December 3, 2001 - Nadine Strossen
description: Jon begins with Operation Enduring Coverage and looks at some of the more quaint ways Americans are making their presence felt in Afghanistan. IT is here and transportation will never be the same. Mo Rocca tries IT out on the streets of New York and his data is, well, inconclusive. Steve Carell travels the nooks and crannies of America to make up stories about the little people. Nadine Strossen uses Jon as a warm up for Congress.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: December 4, 2001 - John Edward
description: Jon whittles a menorah out of a pumpernickel bagel to celebrate the holiday season. Homeland Security raises the terror advisory threat to celebrate the holiday. John Walker Lindh is caught with the Taliban and Mo Rocca knows exactly why it happened. If Lindh is lucky, Fox News's newest embedded correspondent, Geraldo Rivera, will get an exclusive interview. Steve Carell and Nancy Walls are up in arms about People's "Sexiest Man" and John Edward can talk to your dead relatives.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: December 5, 2001 - Marg Helgenberger
description: Operation Enduring Coverage covers the currently mistake-ridden but soon-to-be gaffe-free establishment of an interim government in Afghanistan. Harvard University inflates its grades. Mo Rocca is shocked to learn that George Washington was not the first president of the United States, and Jon takes a closer look at how Enron destroyed its employees' lives. Steve Carell shows us the difference between good and bad advertising, Strom Thurmond has been alive for a very long time, and Marg Helgenberger is the perfect shiksa.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: December 6, 2001 - Ted Danson
description: Steve Carell reports from Kandahar, Afghanistan. The U.S. military develops new smart bombs. Senior Defense Analyst Matt Walsh investigates Osama bin Laden's hidden fortress. Commentator Lewis Black examines holiday shopping catalogs, while the bi - monthly Jon Magazine returns. Ted Danson talks about his dog's eye surgery.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: December 10, 2001 - Stephen Colbert as Al Sharpton
description: U.S. advisors are closing in on Osama bin Laden, and Lauren Weedman investigates the mystery of the Choccolocco monster in Alabama. Phillip Morris releases a new holiday cigarette and Nancy Walls discusses the different holidays in December. For Jon Stewart's interview, Stephen Colbert pretends to be Al Sharpton.
season_title: 6: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

description: Brian Williams reports a false story on NBC News. Jon Stewart presents news from around the world: comic books in Egypt, weddings in England, cigars in Cuba and celebrations in the Easter Islands. Lewis Black comments on proposed slogans for New York City. The Rock talks about his love for destruction.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 3, 2005 - Ari Fleischer
description: The AARP isn't going to support privatization, despite the Republicans' new, young publicity tool for Social Security reform. Rob Corddry details the three steps to New Journalism and undergoes a radical transformation. Former White House Press sSecretary Ari Fleischer talks about his new book, "Taking The Heat," and the back - and - forth that goes on between the White House press corps and the Bush administration.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 7, 2005 - Melissa Boyle Mahle
description: Jon Stewart is not impressed with new CIA Director Porter Goss' enthusiasm. Senior Domestic Affaires correspondent Samantha Bee and Senior Martha Stewart correspondent Rob Corddry report on Martha Stewart's release from prison and her house arrest in Bedford, NY. The Presidents of Lebanon and Syria hammer out a timetable for the withdrawal of Syrian forces after 29 years of occupation. Lewis Black comments on the E! channel's re-enactment of the Michael Jackson trial. Jon interviews former CIA field operative Melissa Boyle Mahle and they discuss the current state of the CIA.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 8, 2005 - Brian Williams
description: Deborah Norville breaks the rules and faces the consequences. Martha Stewart is released from prison, Stephen Colbert looks at the challenges Stewart will face now that she's free and Brian Williams has some beef with Jon for making fun of him.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 9, 2005 - Bruce Willis
description: Rappers 50 Cent and The Game end their extended feud while the Lebanese people protest the Syrian occupation of their country. Stephen Colbert gives up the God Machine for Lent, and Bruce Willis discusses his new movie, "Hostage."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 10, 2005 - Paul Krugman
description: Michael Jackson arrives late to his child molestation trial and Dan Rather resigns his position as CBS News anchor. The SAT exam is revised and John Bolton is nominated for United Nations ambassador. Children read the transcripts from news pundits. Paul Krugman predicts the outcome of Social Security privatization.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 14, 2005 - Harry G. Frankfurt
description: Jon Stewart explores the congressional hearings on steroids in baseball. Samantha Bee looks at the controversy spawned by Clint Eastwood's "Million Dollar Baby." Egyptian scientists have discovered that King Tut was a klutz and Harry Frankfurt visits the set to talk about bullsh*t.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 15, 2005 - Tom Fenton
description: Condoleezza Rice will not run for president. Bob Wiltfong travels to the Texas town Dr. Phil has adopted and Tom Fenton believes the news industry is in worse shape than he's ever seen it before.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 16, 2005 - Al Green
description: President George W. Bush nominates Paul Wolfowitz to replace current World Bank President James Wolfensohn, and Chief International Finance correspondent Ed Helms reports on this development. Correspondent Rob Corddry checks in from the Michael Jackson child molestation trial in California, and Reverend Al Green talks about his new album, "Everything's Ok."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 17, 2005 - Craig Ferguson
description: Bono may be considered for president of the World Bank. Northern Ireland still struggles with the troubles between Catholics and Protestants and Rob Corddry looks into the IRA's latest scandal. Lewis Black has lost faith in America's institutions. Craig Ferguson talks to Jon about "The Late Late Show."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 21, 2005 - Sandra Bullock
description: Congress passes legislation to bring the Schiavo case in front of a federal judge, and President Bush returns early from his vacation to sign it. Senior Ethicist Stephen Colbert explains why Washington leaders should travel around the country solving people's personal problems. Maine State Representative Brian Duprey wants to propose anti-gay bills so he can turn around and defeat them in congress. Sandra Bullock talks about her new movie and mocks the size of Jon's penis.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 22, 2005 - Catherine Keener
description: Rick Sanchez of CNN does some hard hitting investigative journalism on what being stunned with 50,000 volts feels like. The Bush Administration values the kind of facts that go above the filter and Rob Corddry reveals the origins of that same filter. Lewis Black weighs in on steroid use in baseball and laments the state of the game. Catherine Keener and Jon became very close friends working on movie that no one saw.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 23, 2005 - Ozzy Osbourne
description: Barry Bonds blames the media for all his recent troubles while Donald Rumsfeld blames his inferiors for all of the mistakes he made in Iraq. Steve Carell reports on a dangerous mission he undertook in Iraq. France wants the Olympics, Vietnam doesn't want bird flu and some New Zealand women really want Prince Charles. Jon talks to Ozzy Osbourne about the finale of "The Osbournes" and his new CD box set, "Prince of Darkness."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: March 24, 2005 - RZA
description: The Supreme Court refuses to intervene in the Schiavo case, Ed Helms investigates investigative journalism on the campus of Rutgers, the Vatican crusades against "The DaVinci Code" and RZA talks about his philosophy and his new book.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 4, 2005 - Reggie Miller
description: The Daily Show sends Rob Corddry to the Vatican to cover the death of Pope John Paul II. Fox News Channel prematurely calls the pope's death and starts pointing fingers while Stephen Colbert uses his fingers to illustrate the church and the steeple's process of electing a new pontiff. Reggie Miller stops by to offer Jon a hand in slam dunking. "Produce Pete" Steve Carell drops in after a 14 month absence to discuss cabbage.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 5, 2005 - Thomas Friedman
description: A new 9/11 commission report is released on the process of U.S. government intelligence gathering. Senior correspondent Rob Corddry revisits the kid with the big head. President George W. Bush has not laid out a Social Security plan. New York Times columnist Thomas Friedman believes the international economic playing field is being flattened by the Internet.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 6, 2005 - Matthew McConaughey
description: Jon Stewart sounds off on Tom DeLay and John Cornyn's desire to strike back at judicial decisions they don't like. The Iraqis elect a man named Talabani to govern and Samantha Bee is bored out of her mind watching reconstruction. Alberto Gonzales and Robert Mueller still want to use the Patriot Act to keep a close eye on library records. The final installment in the "Star Wars" series is on its way to theatres and Hasbro is introducing the toys to match it. Matthew McConaughey likes to float down the Amazon.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 7, 2005 - Drew Barrymore
description: Millions of mourners flock to Vatican City to pay tribute to Pope John Paul II. Ed Helms reports that Italian officials are handling the influx of pilgrims with their famous organizational skills, while the passing of John Paul II turns out to be a wonderful time to point out how his views coincided exactly with those of many conservatives. Lewis Black examines the celebrities who can't wait to tell us what's going on in the world and Drew Barrymore talks about filming during real Red Sox games in Fenway Park.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 11, 2005 - Byron York
description: Prince Charles marries Camilla Parker Bowles. Stephen Colbert reports on Floridian David Spears, who is discriminated against because of the color of his tattooed skin. Ex-politicians will apparently do anything after they retire. Byron York talks to Jon about his book "The Vast Left Wing Conspiracy."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 12, 2005 - Bob Dole
description: President George W. Bush has "My Sharona" on his iPod. Handshaking and NAMBLA controversies erupt during Pope John Paul's funeral. Daily Show Senior Papalogist Stephen Colbert explains the ins and outs of the papal election. Lewis Black comments on nationalist rioting and its various ineffective methods. Senator Bob Dole presents his new book, "One Soldier's Story," in which he talks about his tour of duty in World War II and the injuries he sustained.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 13, 2005 - John P. Avlon
description: Jon profiles a beluga whale that likes to party. John Bolton is all but nominated to the post of ambassador to the United Nations. Ed Helms travels across the country to find out what it's gonna take to get Muslims to like America. New York Sun columnist John P. Avlon discusses his book "Independent Nation." Children read from a transcript of "Hannity & Colmes" in which Sean Hannity demands that radio host John Sylvester apologize for calling Condoleezza Rice "Aunt Jemima."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 14, 2005 - David Duchovny
description: Jon reports on a little public interest story about a woman who found a finger in her Wendy's chili. Iraqi citizens vote in their new president, Jalal Talabani. Secretary of Defense Donald Rumsfeld visits Baghdad and President Bush visits the servicemen at Fort Hood, TX. Jon covers a recent mandate for U.S. labs to destroy the Influenza AH2N2 virus and explores the new focus on healthy foods at Sesame Street. Iran hires women police officers, Bobby Fischer offers a conspiracy theory for his arrest in Japan.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 18, 2005 - Robert Reich
description: 115 Roman Catholic cardinals gather in the Sistine Chapel to choose the next pope, Stephen Colbert gives your blind faith that little bit of physical evidence it needs to keep it going with This Week in God, and former Secretary of Labor Reich discusses his new book, "Reason."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 19, 2005 - Sarah Vowell
description: A new pope has been elected and Jon is disappointed it isn't Joe Lieberman. Coverage of the papal coronation gets off to a spotty start as pundits are unable to determine if the smoke is white or black. Conservative strategist Frank Luntz takes on Samantha Bee as his protégé, and she in turn orchestrates a foul - mouthed town meeting. Eye On Breasts takes a look at the re - legalization of silicon breast implants as Charlie Sheen and the rackless rejoice. Sarah Vowell drops by to discuss some of the lesser-known presidential assassinations.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 20, 2005 - Dennis Miller
description: Tom DeLay faces charges of corruption and his friendship with the president is questioned. Rob Corddry gives a lap dance to a Harvard student. Dennis Miller bashes the new pope and gets fired up about the war in Iraq and global warming.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 21, 2005 - Reza Aslan
description: Jon starts with some sad news about Paris Hilton's announced dissolution of her friendship with Nicole Richie. The Department of Agriculture releases twelve new food pyramids, much to the delight of fitness expert Denise Austin. John Bolton's nomination to the UN ambassadorship is in question after Republican George Voinovich signals the Non-Partisan Alert. Rob Corddry is worse for wear after an interview with Bolton. Jon then explores the history of new pope and ex-Hitler Youth Benedict XVI. Two children reenact a debate on sexual orientation between Jerry Falwell and Chris Matthews. Moptopped Reza Aslan joins Jon to explain the state of Islam and how its internal conflicts affect its external ones.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 25, 2005 - Floyd Abrams
description: Jon calls out college professors who show The Daily Show instead of teaching their classes. Thunderstorms and hail prevent President Bush from reaching an Earth Day celebration, while liberals protest his administration's environmental policy with ice cream. Ed Helms swims down the drain to the Cayman Islands to explore tropical tax breaks. Jon catches up with Colin Powell and John Edwards, who are enjoying sports while out of the spotlight. Floyd Abrams sits with Jon to go through the history and future of free speech in America.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 26, 2005 - Ice Cube
description: Jon Stewart presents a very special message to young chimps. Senators combine church and state in a mega-church, and as Correspondent Stephen Colbert reports, that's delicious. The latest installment of Gaywatch covers gay marriage, foster child restrictions and boycotts. Guest Ice Cube gives Jon some parenting advice.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 27, 2005 - Christina Hoff Sommers
description: The President speaks of alternate energy sources at a Small Business Association meeting, but ends up rehashing solutions from the past. Samantha Bee investigates a small business that figured out a smoking ban could save them some healthcare dollars. Jon explores the world of transportation, where the largest passenger jet features a bar and the fastest passenger train features bad brakes. Christina Hoff Sommers stops by to tell Jon about the overprotection of America's youth and the endangerment of dodgeball.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: April 28, 2005 - Steven Levitt
description: The U.S. military confiscates the laptop of insurgency leader Abu Musab al - Zarqawi but finds little more than porn. Donald Rumsfeld fends off reporter's questions with a trademark blend of corporate mumbo - jumbo and Orwellian doublespeak. Jon Stewart takes a perfunctory look around the rest of the non - Iraq world, including the many bans of China. Economist Steven Levitt talks about his new book "Freakonomics" and posits his theory connecting Roe v. Wade to a drop in crime.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 2, 2005 - Zell Miller
description: Jon begins with a warning to the Netherlands that The Daily Show is merely a fake news show. George W. Bush out-funnies "Joey" on primetime with a speech about alternate energy sources and social security. A few days later President Bush shows up at the White House Correspondents Dinner, where the first lady delivers a racy speech. Stephen Colbert was there for Mrs. Bush's midnight show and plays a secret tape of a far more ribald version of her speech. The media jumps to conclusions on the runaway bride case. Zell Miller talks with Jon about decency in America from a cultural and economic perspective.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 3, 2005 - Christiane Amanpour
description: Alaska Senator Ted Stevens attempts to place FCC restrictions on cable television. and Stephen Colbert travels to Mississippi where a local candidate named Rick James keeps having his campaign signs vandalized Lewis Black explores tourism at Las Vegas's most expensive casino and abroad with Drew Barrymore.. Christiane Amanpour discusses elections and being a female reporter in the Middle East.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 5, 2005 - Martin Short
description: Prime Minister Tony Blair hopes to gain an historic third term but first must sweat out a rigorous town hall meeting.Stephen Colbert reports on the ungodly British democratic process. Arkansas bird-watchers rediscover the once-thought-extinct Ivory-Billed Woodpecker, Produce Pete Steve Carell extols the virtues of raw seaweed and Martin Short discusses his new movie "Jiminy Glick In Lalawood."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 5, 2005 - Tom Ridge
description: Tony Blair is elected Britain's Prime Minister for a third term and "Primetime: Live" investigates an "American Idol" scandal. Pat O'Brien discusses his alcoholism on "The Dr. Phil Show." Former Secretary of Homeland Security, Tom Ridge, reports on the colored terror alert system, and children read transcripts from MSNBC's "Scarborough Country."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 9, 2005 - Kathleen Turner
description: Jon has some tips for Michael Jackson's legal team. President Bush travels to Russia and joyrides around Vladimir Putin's estate. Bob Wiltfong dives headlong into the world of sexy cheerleading. Governor Arnold Schwarzenegger's approval rating takes a dive, so Sean Hannity takes it upon himself to try and raise it back up. Jon interviews Kathleen Turner about playing the title role in Edward Albee's "Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf?" on Broadway.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 10, 2005 - Wanda Sykes
description: President Bush signs a law opening America's national forests up to logging and road building. Samantha Bee heads to Atlantic City to win back her unfertilized eggs. The cable news channels figure out that blogs exist, Rob Corddry provides up - to - the - millisecond coverage of what's happening in the blogosphere and Wanda Sykes talks about juggling babies on the set of "Monster - in - Law."
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 11, 2005 - Al Roker
description: A Cessna flies into Washington, D.C.'s restricted airspace causing people to run for their lives. North Korean Dictator Kim Jong-il prepares to test nuclear weapons by digging a huge hole. Stephen Colbert uses his God Machine to discuss a multitude of spiritual issues. Lewis Black rants about world leaders and then focuses on mocking dictator Kim Jong-il. Children read aloud a transcript of an interview between Chris Matthews and the Reverend Jerry Falwell in which they discuss Falwell's views on homosexuality. Al Roker presents his book "Big Shoes" and discusses the role of fatherhood.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 12, 2005 - Tracy Ullman
description: Senator George Voinovich offers several reasons why John Bolton is the worse choice for U.N. ambassador, but decides to vote him in anyway. Florida passes a law that allows citizens to fire a gun whenever they feel threatened. Ed Helms looks into a new philanthropy program, "Guns for Tots," and Spokane Mayor Jim West is forcibly outted. Tracey Ullman stops by and enjoys being herself rather than one of her characters for a change.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 31, 2005 - Gerald Posner
description: Jon Stewart and the show are back from two weeks off and Jon's missed a lot of opportunities for unique facial expressions. The Army is getting most of its intelligence in Iraq from the enemies' blog. Rob Corddry drives his sick ride all over town to look at rising oil prices. Gerald Posner is in the studio to talk about the crippling and corrupting relationship America has with Saudi Arabia.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 1, 2005 - Bo Bice
description: The identity of Deep Throat is revealed and Senior Scandal Historian Stephen Colbert recounts his own coverage of Watergate. House Majority Leader Tom DeLay is honored by the American Conservatives Union. A team of British and South Korean scientists announce a new, more efficient process of producing cloned embryos. "American Idol" runner - up Bo Bice shares backstage stories from his tour.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 2, 2005 - Russell Crowe
description: The war in Iraq isn't going too well, but don't tell the Bush Administration, it might ruin their day. Ed Helms stages the re-enactment of a man who resuscitated his dead chicken. Russell Crowe knows that there are worse things than being hit in the face and Steve Carell's Produce Pete laments his unfortunate banana incident.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 6, 2005 - Newt Gingrich
description: Jon Stewart tells Russell Crowe how to take care of a hotel concierge. Ed Helms is in California to report on Michael Jackson's collision with reality. Stephen Colbert looks at the Aztec's God "This Week in God." The French are being their contrarian selves again and Newt Gingrich is not going to announce his candidacy for president on this show.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 7, 2005 - Steven Johnson
description: The Supreme Court passes new medical marijuana laws. U.S. Marines uncover an Iraqi rebel bunker and Senior Subterranean Structural Analyst Stephen Colbert is on site with his report. Correspondent Ed Helms revisits the chairman of the NY Libertarian Party, and author Steven Johnson discusses the benefits of our current pop culture.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 8, 2005 - Colin Powell
description: Jon Stewart promises that he'll be a classy drunk for his interview with former Secretary of State Colin Powell. Prime Minister Tony Blair doesn't get quite the commitment he needs from President George W. Bush for African aid and global warming reduction measures. Senior White House Correspondent Rob Corddry takes a closer look at the growing distance between the prime minister and the president. Former Secretary of State Colin Powell speaks candidly about the quality of the U.S. intelligence leading up to the Iraq War, the opinions of his colleagues, and his relationship with the president since leaving the Bush administration.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 9, 2005 - Matt Lauer
description: Jon Stewart marvels at the power of Angelina Jolie's love. General Motors uses corporate doublespeak to announce cutbacks in jobs, and Samantha Bee travels to Quebec, where Wal - Mart has closed a store rather than deal with a union. The New York Jets and Mr. Met are denied a stadium, and San Francisco is offended by the shoddy editing of the 49ers' PR man. Matt Lauer supports his Discovery Channel special 'Greatest American' by bashing many of their selections, including Dr. Phil and John Edwards.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 13, 2005 - Larry Diamond
description: Michael Jackson is found not guilty in his child molestation trial. Ronald McDonald discusses his healthier image on MSNBC. Democratic National Committee Chairman Nominee Howard Dean makes offensive remarks about Republicans and Senior Political Analyst Ed Helms analyzes the situation. Jon Stewart in his International Pamphlet brings news about Kim Jong-il in North Korea, surgery in China, casual clothes in Japan and the Live 8 concert in London. Author Larry Diamond breaks down the situation in Iraq.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 14, 2005 - Will Ferrell
description: Michael Jackson is acquitted on all ten counts of child molestation. Rob Corddry is outside the Neverland estate to tell about the Caligulan celebration that followed Jackson's acquittal. Jon Stewart takes a look at the level of incompetence the cable news shows legal analysts exhibit while awaiting the verdict and Senior Child Molestation Analyst Stephen Colbert reports on why California is the place to commit a crime. Will Ferrell is on the show to promote a movie that's not even getting released and children read the words of pundits.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 15, 2005 - Flynt Leverett
description: Lawmakers call for the shut down of prisons on Guantanamo Bay. Ed Helms reports on the Speedo controversy in Cape May, New Jersey. Flynt Leverett talks about his book "Inheriting Syria" and the political situation in the Middle East. A preview of the Colbert Report gives a taste of Stephen's new show.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 16, 2005 - Kenneth Timmerman
description: The Patriot Act's most controversial provisions are due to expire and President Bush has launched a campaign to permanently renew them. Jon wants everyone to stop comparing their enemies to Hitler, and Kenneth Timmerman believes Osama bin Laden is in Iran.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 20, 2005 - Ringo Starr
description: After discussing the intensity of Tom Cruise and Katie Holmes, Jon Stewart lets us know that the FBI and CIA might not be doing the best job with terrorism but are doing just fine with organic gardening. Ed Helms disagrees with the terrorist part (not the gardening part) and Rob Corddry tries to understand why security procedures are so demanding for tourists and why everyone hates America so much. The first recorded map labeling our continent "America" is auctioned off at Christie's in London, and Ringo Starr drops by to talk about recording music and choosing love.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 21, 2005 - Dwight Yoakam
description: President Bush's lunch with European Union officials is ruined by a reporter who brings up the "I" word.. Bush later joins with Blair in denying a Downing street memo while Democrats attempt to uncover the truth in a basement. Lewis Black is surprised at how anyone can get a book deal but is unsurprised that the reason is usually money.Jon Stewart helps Dwight Yoakam connect monkeys to The Monkees.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 22, 2005 - Bill Moyers
description: Hyperbolic rhetoric rules the day. Dick Durban compares the American treatment of detainees at Guantanamo Bay to Nazi's treatment of prisoners during the Holocaust. Indiana Republican John Hostettler takes to the floor of the House of Representatives to decry the historically unfair treatment of Christians. Samantha Bee looks into why so many American kids are acting like pussies, Bill Moyers wants a job at Comedy Central and children read the words of pundits.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 23, 2005 - Howard Dean
description: Jon Stewart wonders how many times the Republicans can bring up September 11th while endorsing a constitutional amendment banning flag burning. Stephen Colbert finds out about another traditional Democratic stronghold that has fled to the Republican's big tent. Howard Dean visits the show to talk about the Democratic Party's new plans to overthrow the Republican monolith.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 27, 2005 - Hanna Rosin
description: The Bush administration defends Dick Cheney's assertion that the Iraq insurgency is in its last throes by re-defining the word 'throe,' and Stephen Colbert is more than happy to continue their word game. Jon takes a relatively closer look at the Bush agenda and how the media, Democrats and the American people block it. Hanna Rosin follows around the politicians of the future.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 28, 2005 - Morgan Spurlock
description: The Supreme Court has nothing against religious interior decorators unless they're working on government buildings. Jon Stewart highlights issues in the states of California, Utah and Alaska. Lewis Black comments on free medical advice offered by people who haven't been to medical school, and author Morgan Spurlock talks about his new book and television show.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 11, 2005 - Marci Hamilton
description: London's bomb attack scares Americans, and Rob Corddry reports on the aftermath of the bombings from England. Sandra Day O'Connor announces her retirement. Ed Helms travels to Florida where some controversial art is being displayed at the Controversy Exhibition. Author Marci Hamilton tells Jon about the legal privileges religion receives.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 12, 2005 - Matt Taibbi
description: Karl Rove leaks Valerie Plame's name to told Robert Novak and Rove is in hot water. Scott McClellan forcefully dodges questions about the Valerie Plame case. Author Matt Taibbi talks about his time working undercover on George W. Bush's presidential campaign.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 13, 2005 - Bernard Goldberg
description: The top reporters blanket Florida to cover Hurricane Dennis, Stephen Colbert tracks hurricane footage from The Daily Show's Storm Tracker Tracker and Bernard Goldberg argues with Jon over the cultural environment.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 14, 2005 - Michael Isikoff
description: Jon addresses the audience reaction to the new set. Congress cuts $50 million from the mass transit national security budget and votes to distribute a significant amount of Homeland Security money to states equally, rather than by risk-factor. A Canadian bookstore accidentally sells 14 copies of "Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince" prior to the official sales date, and Rob Corddry goes undercover to see if it could happen here. Jon looks at daredevil feats of skateboarding in China and feats of gluttony in Coney Island, NY. Michael Isikoff talks about what he sees as the real criminal issues of the Valerie Plame identity leak.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 18, 2005 - Bob Woodward & Carl Bernstein
description: Debates rage on Sunday morning political talk shows as to who is smearing who in the Valerie Plame CIA leak case. Samantha Bee stages a re-enactment of the Valerie Plame drama in spectacular detail, dancers and singers included. Bob Woodward and Carl Bernstein discuss their new book and their thoughts about the current political climate.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 19, 2005 - Billy Bob Thorton
description: Karl Rove takes the hit for the Valerie Plame leak and if it were up to Congressman Peter King, he'd get a medal. Lewis Black reminds us of the political pet causes that keep government officials busy. Ed Helms meets with fitness expert Vicki Mackarvich who has been prescribed vagina cream to put on her face as the key to immortality, and Billy Bob Thornton talk about " Bad News Bears" and his favorite presidential depictions.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 20, 2005 - Robert F. Kennedy, Jr.
description: Jon delivers a eulogy for the old Daily Show couch. The press is sure George Bush's newest Supreme Court nominee will be Edith Brown Clement, but it turns out to be John Roberts. Ed Helms wonders why Bush would choose such a white nominee, while the network talking heads call for a no-holds-barred partisan battle over the Roberts nomination. Rob Corddry analyzes failed Supreme Court nominations past and Robert F. Kennedy, Jr. discusses the link between childhood vaccinations and autism.
season_title: 10: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
