title: May 14, 2007 - Jeremy Paxman
description: Bush conducts a student orchestra, Jon and a Senate committee reduce Attorney General Alberto Gonzales into a single phrase, Rob Riggle pleads the fifth on Bush administration investigations, Samantha Bee probes Mormonism in This Week in God and BBC journalist Jeremy Paxman makes a backhanded case for the British monarchy.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 15, 2007 - Tim Russert
description: Jon chastises presidential candidates who make the pundit rounds on Mothers Day. Jason Jones visits a derma-surgeon and spin doctor for campaign trail advice. Jon gives his take on the militarys YouTube and MySpace ban. Tim Russert discusses the Bush administrations evasion of Meet the Press.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 16, 2007 - Don Rickles
description: Jason Jones introduces heavily edited blooper reels of Republican presidential candidates. Jon pulls out the concessions for the 24-inspired scenarios at the Republican debates. Sam Bee runs down the list of NILF hotties anchoring the 24 hour news networks. Don Rickles shares his adventures in film and stand-up.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 17, 2007 - Brink Lindsey
description: Jon reacts to the news of Prince Harrys non-deployment to Iraq. James Comeys story about the Presidents wiretapping program and the strong-arming of a bedridden John Ashcroft leads to Jons dubbing of a telenovela. John Hodgman examines Bushs many uses of Im Looking Forward to It. Libertarian academic Brink Lindsey examines the aftereffects of Baby Boomer-era prosperity.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 21, 2007 - Zaki Chehab
description: Jason Jones files a roll call of the combatants in Lebanon. Jon gives a fond look back to the Bush/Blair marriage to the sounds of Dirty Dancing. Larry Wilmore and John Oliver profile public apologies. Journalist Zaki Chehab argues that the U.S. should enforce the moderates in the Middle East.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 22, 2007 - Margaret Spellings
description: Jon lays into the new immigration bill that brings out the Foghorn Leghorn in one Senator. Aasif Mandvi trots out the countrys new immigration point system and slogan. Dan Bakkedahl enrolls in a Mexican border crossing simulation. U.S. Secretary of Education Margaret Spellings gets a pop SAT question from Lunchable-snacking Jon.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 23, 2007 - Kevin Robbins
description: Jon declares the Democrats pussies after the removal of timetables from the Iraq war funding bill. John Oliver covers Presidential snaps after Jimmy Carters criticism of the worst administration ever. Jon covers radioactive poisoning murders in the former Soviet Union. Commander of the Thunderbirds, the U.S. Air Force Air Demonstration Squadron, Lt. Col. Kevin Robbins offers Jon a ride and a jumpsuit.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: May 24, 2007 - Al Gore
description: Rob Riggle goes into Mad Max mode to report on rising gas prices. Jon circumnavigates the testimony of the U.S. attorney firing scandal. Al Gore drops by to lambaste the media and dub Jon court jester of the realm.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 4, 2007 - Ron Paul
description: Jon shares his vacation adventures to Greece with TB-carrying Andrew Speaker, then blasts CNNs coverage of the Democratic debate. John Edwards tries to separate himself from Hillary and Barack while Joe Biden stance on gays in the military digs him into a hole. Jon talks to Hustlers Larry Flynt about his $1 million bounty on Republican dirt. Republican presidential candidate Ron Paul drops by to outline his free market beliefs and opposition to the Iraq war.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 5, 2007 - Paul Rudd
description: Jon reads the Scooter Libby sentencing and the four @#%holes who wrote character statements, covers the Congressman William Jefferson bribery scandal and announces the conservative bases final abandonment of President Bush. Rob Riggle exposes the city of Anaheims plans to build low-income housing next to Disneyland. Paul Rudd shows up in a tux in anticipation of the Tony Awards and promotes Knocked Up.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 6, 2007 - Michael Barone
description: The Giant Head of Ted Koppel wonders if Jon read the book from tonights guest. The third Republican Presidential candidate debate makes Bushs policies look moderate. John Oliver divines the lightning bolt during Giulianis answer. Lewis Black looks at creepy surveillance tech. Writer and historian Michael Barone discusses the religious and political upheaval that inspired the Bill of Rights.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 7, 2007 - Eddie Izzard
description: The team gives a headline for the Paris Hiltons imprisonment without the coverage. The London 2012 Olympics logo gets the once-over. Jon jokes about the G8 summit in Germany with its anti-protestor water tactics and the Bush/Putin feud. Samantha Bee reports on NASCARs Garnier Fructis sponsorship. Eddie Izzard weaves an American Revolutionary War critique into his pitch for The Riches on iTunes.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 11, 2007 - David Steinberg
description: Jon calls CNN out on its coverage of Paris Hilton over Peter Pace, then shows Albanias love for President Bush. Jason Jones reports on the meeting between the Pope and President. John Hodgman shares his expertise of mixed martial arts. Comedian David Steinberg charts his career and tells a story about Milton Berles Friars Club Roast.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 12, 2007 - Robert Shrum
description: Jon canvasses Senatorial hi-jinks with the tortured, anticlimactic death of the immigration reform bill and the no confidence vote on Attorney General Alberto Gonzales. Sam Bee investigates whether Americas ready for a Mormon President. Democratic political consultant Robert Shrum dishes some dirt on formal presidential candidates and going with the gut.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 13, 2007 - Allan Brandt
description: Mess OPotamia  The militarys plan to arm Sunni insurgents prompts Jon to chart our list of friends and enemies in Iraq. Aasif Mandvi thinks the re-bombing of the mosque in Samarra is a positive sign. Larry Wilmore takes on the role of Senior Mexican Correspondent to call out Immigration Reform for what it is. Harvard Medical School professor Allan Brandt runs down some shameless sales initiatives from the tobacco industry.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 14, 2007 - Angelina Jolie
description: Jon tries to bring past and present Tony Snow together. ClusterF@#k to the Whitehouse  Jon visits the online hangouts of John McCain, Rudy Giuliani, Barack Obama, Mitt Romney and submits a theme song to Hillarys campaign. Stewart skewers a fear-mongering commercial for a local Oklahoma meteorologist. Angelina Jolie drops by to promote A Normal Heart and ends up signing Jons scribble prenup.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 18, 2007 - Steve Carell
description: Warportunity in the Middle East. Jon spells out the difference between Fatah and Hamas. Aasif Mandvi asserts that the Palestinians must replicate American history for democracy to thrive. Rob Riggle introduces his movie segment, if only to slag on Steve Carell. Meanwhile, Steve Carell drops by with butler in tow to reminisce about post-9/11 Daily Show bits and Produce Pete.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 19, 2007 - Brian Williams
description: The giant head of Ted Koppel confirms Jons suckiness. Stewart extends the media-created metaphor of an Iraq whack-a-mole strategy. Sam Bee investigates anti-war American insurgents among us. Brian Williams makes a return visit with giant head stories and a sobering account of his latest trip to Iraq.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 20, 2007 - Fareed Zakaria
description: Hillary Clinton picks a campaign theme song and Jon loses again. Potential presidential candidates Bloomberg, Fred Thompson and more pique the curiosity of the media  and Jons ire. The Vatican issues Ten Commandments for the road, and John Oliver shows off the latest breathalyzer. Newsweek International editor Fareed Zakaria expands on Jons Middle East Frat Party analogy. Stephen Colbert uses West Side Story as inspiration for the throw.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 21, 2007 - Greg Bear
description: Jon breaks out the glowsticks for Obamas new ringtones, then roasts the Democratic candidates during their visit to the American Federation of State County and Municipal Employees Union. Next Jon delivers a graduation speech at the Taliban suicide bomber school commencement. Rob Riggle reports from Amsterdam about shrinking American stature (literally). Sci-fi author Greg Bear visits to scare the bejebus out of Jon with emergent technologies and the possibility of more domestic terrorism.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 25, 2007 - Steve Vogel
description: Dick Cheney tries to absolve himself from a scandal by claiming hes not a full part of the executive branch, and Jon shows us what the Vice Presidents finger is for. John Oliver traces Cheneys mythical forms over the years. Jason Jones investigates a veteran who gave George Bush his Purple Heart in the war of words. Author Steve Vogel shares stories about the politics behind the construction of the Pentagon.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 26, 2007 - Bruce Willis
description: Jon introduces a new segment about the Vice President called You Dont Know Dick and wonders what he needs with a man-sized safe. Next, Stewart runs down the latest Supreme Court decisions with a flick of the Justice Kennedy Wheel. Sam Bee admits that Justice Cheney is the new deciding vote. Demetri Martin rounds up credit card tips in Trendspotting. Bruce Willis shares stories about working in a New Jersey nuclear power plant and pitches buddy movie ideas with Jon.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 27, 2007 - Michael Moore
description: Jon reveals another "Dick Nugget" -- Cheney had himself removed from the visible world of Google Earth. Giulianis top advisor is busted for trying to share 500 grams of cocaine. Christie Todd Whitman renegs on her post-9/11 air quality claims, Lewis Black joins the Fox news team, and Michael Moore laments being bumped from Larry King for Paris Hilton.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: June 28, 2007 - Claire Danes
description: The U.S. Senate subpoenas Vice President Dick Cheney and revives the immigration debate so that it can kill it once again. Resident Expert John Hodgman breaks the news that illegal aliens have tuberculosis and leprosy. Rob Riggle needs an iPhone, and actress Claire Danes needs a smoke and a drink.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 16, 2007 - Josh Rushing
description: Back from break, Jon is exasperated about Scooter Libby's commuted sentence. Stewart assesses the White House's personal report card on Iraq. Rob Riggle calls the report a "gentleman's F." John Oliver seeks out both sides of the English as Official Language movement. Former military liaison and current Al Jazeera International correspondent Josh Rushing tells what it's like to report from his balanced perspective.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 17, 2007 - Christopher Walken
description: The giant head of Bruce Willis bookends the show with some bad news for Jon. Stewart skewers a Senator caught in the D.C. Madam controversy and Surgeon General nominees under Bush. Sam Bee and Jon report on the the Catholic diocese of L.A.'s payout of its priest sex abuse scandal. Christopher Walken talks about growing up a show boy and cooking for Jon.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 18, 2007 - Matt Groening
description: Jon chastises Michael Vick's dog fighting, then launches into C-Span After Dark coverage about the Senate's Iraq withdrawal filibuster. John Oliver -- nee Olivier -- gives his review of this piece of political theater. Aasif Mandvi reports on the struggles of the Senate's one-night sacrifice. "Simpsons" creator Matt Groening chats about the new movie and answers why Bart hasn't aged.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 19, 2007 - Adam Sandler
description: John Oliver dresses for the final Harry Potter book and drops a spoiler. Al-Qaeda's resurgence forces the Bush Administration to invoke some fuzzy math, while Aasif Mandvi anoints the President as a bodhisattva. Jon says goodbye to Hamas' Mickey Mouse, while Adam Sandler drops by to compare facial hair. Finally, Stephen Colbert gives toilet training encouragement.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 23, 2007 - Neil deGrasse Tyson
description: Jon gives the play-by-play of Dick Cheney's mini-Presidency as Bush undergoes a colonoscopy. Senior Presidential Historian Sam Bee puts Cheney's assumption into perspective of other short-term executives. Crisis averted, Stewart turns his attention to a report from U.S. Ambassador to Iran Ryan Crocker, then tries to separate what Bush is and isn't based on the testimony of his "experts." Astrophysicist Neil deGrasse Tyson blows Jon's mind with talk of bacterium and extraterrestrial life.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 24, 2007 - Robert Pallitto
description: Jon and company cover the first YouTube/CNN debates, ragging on everything from the layout to format. Jason Jones feels alienated from the exclusive coverage. John Oliver submits his own line of questioning in an homage to the Pretty Ricky/Ottoman humping video. Political science professor Robert Pallitto outlines the dangers of Presidential secrecy to the country and Stephen Colbert flubs a throw.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 25, 2007 - Rob Gifford
description: Jon breaks out the gas mask to climb the "K2 of Obfuscation" when Alberto Gonzales takes the stand again. Rob Riggle shows off Diane Feinstein's art therapy project. Lewis Black tackles the Michael Vick/Barry Bonds/NBA ref scandals. NPR reporter Rob Gifford shares his impressions of a changing China. Stephen Colbert apologizes to his toss writer.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 26, 2007 - Robert Dallek
description: Jon saves New Zealanders the trouble of satirizing themselves, then turns his attention to the recent Tour de France doping scandals. John Oliver gives credit to the UK government's handling of the London flood, while Jason Jones reports on the fight to keep mobility scooters for the lazy. Presidential historian Robert Dallek introduces Jon to a whole new Nixon.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 30, 2007 - Alastair Campbell
description: John Oliver poo-poo's Iraq's win in the Asian Cup while Jon notices a grown in Pat Leahy's balls following a Rove subpoena. Aasif Mandvi warns us of America's shrinking scorn supply. Jon gives his impression of Bush's first meeting with new U.K. Prime Minister Gordon Brown. Former press secretary Alastair Campbell defends his former boss Tony Blair in front of Stewart's satire. Stephen Colbert recites a sonnet for the toss.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: July 31, 2007 - Lewis Gordon Pugh
description: A raid on Ted Stevens' Alaskan home yields a rare vintage of wine. Jason Jones rants about how today's legislators are nothing like their old-timey predecessors. John Hodgman gives Jon a primer on Presidential candidate fashion. Aasif Mandvi reports on his foray into the Live Earth concert. Cold water swimmer Lewis Gordon Pugh explains how he doesn't die in arctic conditions.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 1, 2007 - Jed Babbin
description: Donald Rumsfeld and Dick Cheny appear on TV on the same day, doing their dance for Jon, Larry King and Pat Tillman's family. Larry Wilmore breaks down the ins and outs of subprime loans from a black perspective. Conservative Pundit Jed Babbin explains the enemies who the Americans have been soft on for years. Stephen attempts to recite a Homeric epic for the toss.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 2, 2007 - Matt Damon
description: Dick Cheney reveals an object of lust in anther installment of "You Don't Know Dick." Jon profiles small-town eatery adventures on the campaign trail and slips Jon Edwards some anniversary advice. Next, Stewart chimes in on the Obama and Clinton campaigns' manufactured bickering and the subsequent media frenzy. Matt Damon gives as many jabs as he gets from Jon while promoting the Bourne Ultimatum.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 7, 2007 - Andy Samberg
description: Rep. Bob Allen gets caught trying to solicit oral sex and Oliver/Stewart deliver alternatives to his racist alibi. Hillary Clinton digs herself into a lobbyist-based pickle during the YearlyKos convention while the Republican candidates give B.S. answers to admitting their greatest mistakes. Jason Jones investigates a wind farm battle in Nantucket. Andy Samberg relates Internet fame to Jon.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 8, 2007 - Joe Biden
description: Jon salutes Mitt Romney's boys for their patriotic decision to campaign instead of enlist. Rob Riggle uses Barry Bonds' record-breaking home run moment to segue into an escape story. Jon explores the mysteries of the missing oil, money and guns in Iraq. New contributor Buck Henry profiles media moguls throughout the ages. Joe Biden agrees with Jon about the state of the early Democratic debates.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 9, 2007 - Tal Ben-Shahar
description: Neil Cavuto's gushing interview with President Bush has Jon slapping away at the softball questions. Next, Jon goes off on Bush's attempts to explain the explained. Mitt Romney's sons provide harrowing stories from the road for Stewart and Aasif Mandvi. Harvard professor Tal Ben-Shahar has a hard time convincing Jon that his course in Happiness Studies tells us something new.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 13, 2007 - Bill Kristol
description: Karl Rove's resignation announcement sends Jon on a quest to find out exactly who is the "Turd Blossom." John Oliver summons an animated bluebird to show how Rove will be missed. Stewart tries to get brain expert Mony De Leon to give a scientific explanation on the administration's lies. Bill Kristol drops by again to reassure us that the troop surge is going according to the new plan.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 14, 2007 - Denis Leary
description: Condi Rice appoints and special envoy to China, and Jon speaks for us all with a WTF? The Logo Network's debate provides fodder for the most immature gay-themed montage ever. Jon takes the air out of the Iowa Straw Poll. Denis Leary shares stories about aging and watching baseball with Jon. Stephen declares himself unstoppable after hiring Karl Rove during the toss.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 15, 2007 - Stephen F. Hayes
description: Newly elected French President Sarkozy visits the Bush family on vacation and gets his choice of American stereotypes. Sam Bee charts Bush's attack on the Presidential vacation record. Larry Wilmore investigates whether America's ready for a black President with the Jefferson Scale. 2002 Dick Cheney squares off against 1994 Dick Cheney. Finally, Jon flashes a rare show of anger during the interview of Dick Cheney biographer Stephen F. Hayes.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 16, 2007 - John McCain
description: Mattel's recall of Chinese-made toys prompts Jon to find out who the real culprit is. John Oliver shares how he deprived himself of presents on Christmas mornings. Stewart takes aim at Hillary Clinton's secrecy and hospital slumming. John McCain takes Jon's chair for his tenth appearance on the show. Stephen Colbert preps Jon for the upcoming YouTube deposition.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 20, 2007 - Nikolas Kozloff
description: Michael Vick admits his guilt in dog fighting and Jon offers little sympathy. Rob Riggle files his first report from the real Iraq, but not before Aasif Mandvi tries to steal some thunder first. The latest Democratic debate is so boring, ABC has to turn to the other Kucinich to break the monotony. Jon unscrambles Hugo Chavez's six-hour speeches. Author Nikolas Kozloff tries to explain the apparent instability of Chavez. In the toss, Stephen declares that he's moved his entire production to Afghanistan.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 21, 2007 - Alan Weisman
description: Michael Vick may be in more trouble for his gambling than his dog fighting as an incredulous Jon reports. Rob Riggle's tour of Iraq continues with Operation Fluffy Bunny as he compares Iraq to Indiana. Jon recaps a K-Tel version of Karl Rove's greatest hits. Environmental journalist Alan Weisman illustrates what happens to the Earth if the human race was wiped out, and it's not looking good for head lice.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 22, 2007 - Barack Obama
description: Jon spins a much different theme song for Hillary Clinton. Rob Riggle delivers a post card from the troops stationed in Iraq to the vacationing Iraqi parliament. A $20 billion U.S. arms deal to Saudi Arabia leads Jon to a tortured circle of Mideast double-dealing. Sen. Barack Obama addresses early mudslinging and gives the GOP candidates the worst backhanded compliment ever.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: August 23, 2007 - John Nagl
description: President Bush tries to contextualize the Iraq War with World War II and Vietnam, with unprecedented results. Aasif Mandvi shows what would've happened to Maya Lin's Vietnam War Memorial if the U.S. had withdrawn later. Rob Riggle returns from Iraq with highlights during his USO tour. The co-author of the Army's Counterinsurgency Field Manual gives insight into the struggles of fighting the "grad school of war." Stephen razzes Jon for taking a vacation during the toss.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 10, 2007 - Jeff Garlin
description: Sen. Larry Craig drops a follow-up bomb in his anonymous gay bathroom sex scandal, and Rob Corddry files a report after a year in the stakeout. Jon has an R&B crooner sing the background on the rest of the story's coverage. President Bush's secretive trip to Anbar province shows us the one place in Iraq with electricity. Comedian Jeff Garlin repurposes his gift bag since he can't ingest the goodies. Stephen shows off a picture of his speedboat during the toss.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 11, 2007 - Jodie Foster
description: Gen. David Petraeus delivers his report to a fawning press corps and the sounds of Falco while Jon attributes our lack of strategy to MC Escher. Jon Hodgman debuts his new power thinking program. Jodie Foster talks about kids music and the allure of playing a vigilante in "The Brave One."
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 12, 2007 - Robert Draper
description: Vladimir Putin's latest dramatic moves include cheesecake shots and an "enviro-friendly" bomb. A protestor at General Petraeus' testimonial hearing gives Jon flashbacks. Univision's Spanish-language Democratic debate leaves no frontrunner unscathed (in any language). John Oliver shares steely silences with the ambassador to Qatar in the latest installment of "Oliver's Travels." Author Robert Draper amazes Jon with his insight and access to President Bush.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 13, 2007 - Douglas Farah
description: John McCain and Jon trade new names for the former Straight Talk Express. Jon combs Gen. Petraeus' Senate hearings to find a sympathetic voice, and gets a spit-take worthy response from Joe Lieberman. Sam Bee says Happy (Rosh Hashana) New Year and profiles a school founded by a Domino's pizza honcho in This Week in God. Author Douglas Farah's reporting on infamous gunrunner Victor Bout's success leaves Jon feeling inadequate. Stephen is determined to go through with his she-male Emmy plans in the toss.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 18, 2007 - Alan Greenspan
description: OJ Simpson returns to unite the media and relieve us from the sobriety of the real news. Alberto Gonzales gets a send-off from the Justice Department and leaves Jon with a final statement of jaw-dropping irony. Sam Bee pulls her best Sex and the City act to ask whether the U.S. is ready for a female president. Former Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan depresses Jon with a sobering look at human nature.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 19, 2007 - Wesley Clark
description: Jon plays a recording of John Kerry's attempt to get the University of Florida tasing incident under control. Hillary Clinton's health care plan and O.J. Simpson's shenanigans create a flashback opportunity for New Gingrich and a follow-up from Stewart. Larry Wilmore gives up on trying to defend O.J. Gen. Wesley Clark speaks up for Gen. Petraeus and pitches his latest book - even if he's not running for office. Stephen fakes out Jon with the sound of a baby crying in the toss.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 20, 2007 - Bill Clinton
description: President Bush declares Nelson Mandela dead during a press conference over health care. CBS' "Kid Nation" gives Dan Bakkedahl the Xanadu he's always dreamed of. Bill Clinton admits the pleasures of philanthropy and explains why he's campaigning for Hillary in '08.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 24, 2007 - John Bowe
description: Mahmoud Ahmadinejad speaks at Columbia and beats NYC gridlock. The Democrats battle a fly in front of the AARP, while the Republicans manage to creep out the NRA. Buck Henry reflects on primaries of yore. Reporter John Bowe calls attention to modern slavery in America.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 25, 2007 - Evo Morales
description: Hillary Clinton's delayed reaction laugh tracks across five Sunday morning shows. Mahmoud Ahmadinejad's claim that there aren't gays in Iran draws a U.S. parallel from Jon. Dan Bakkedahl investigates the "threat" of Mexican immigration to Canada. Bolivian president Evo Morales cracks Jon up after talk of agrarian reform.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 26, 2007 - Jamie Foxx
description: Jon is impressed with Bolivian president Evo Morales from the previous evening. The media's showdown between President Bush and Mahmoud Ahmadinejad fails to materialize. Aasif Mandvi decodes U.N. delegate body language. Lewis Black goes off on counterfeiters and fake veterans. Jamie Foxx talks about the luxuries of shooting in Dubai and the buddy cop movie he'll shoot with Jon.
season_title: 12: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart
series_title: The Daily Show with Jon Stewart

title: September 27, 2007 - Ken Burns
